Limpopo families who lost members and relatives are expected to meet with the team investigating the crash. eNCA's Nqobile Madlala has more on that story. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Families of the 17 victims who died in a horrific accident in Limpopo are yet to find out if they'll be burying their loved ones. Provincial officials are assisting with the identification process of the victims that were burnt beyond recognition. READ: Process to identify Limpopo crash victims set to begin on Thursday The crash happened between a 22-seater bus and an SUV near Mookgophong. Family members visited the accident scene on Thursday.